---
description: Project context. Always loaded for every conversation.
alwaysApply: true
---
Read @PRD.md before starting any task. It contains the mission,
tech stack, data model, features, acceptance criteria, and conventions.

Read @CLAUDE.md for repo structure, key commands, and deployment config.

If a /mockups directory exists with design files, check the relevant
mockup before building or modifying any UI component. Match the mockup
layout and visual hierarchy.

When starting a new feature, first identify which Feature section in
the PRD it corresponds to. Follow its acceptance criteria as your
definition of done.

Always follow the conventions listed in PRD.md. If a convention
conflicts with your default behavior, the PRD wins.
